tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;"> the price of Bitcoin goes up</a>. One possible rea=
son for this is that Elon Musk is a rich famous weird guy with a fandom; pe=
ople pay attention to what he does and get entertainment out of it. When he=
 seems to have fun with Bitcoin, other people say =E2=80=9Chey Bitcoin look=
s fun=E2=80=9D and buy Bitcoin, so the price of Bitcoin goes up.</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another possible reason is that Elon Musk is the chie=
f executive officer of=C2=A0two big influential futuristic companies, and h=
e plays a role in shaping the possible future of the global economy. If Tes=
la Inc. announced that you can only pay for Teslas in Bitcoin, or if SpaceX=
 announced that the only legal tender on Mars will be Bitcoin, that would b=
e good for Bitcoin demand. There is a sort of future-of-the-galactic-econom=
y case for Bitcoin that Elon Musk can bolster. And in fact Tesla has said t=
hat it will (non-exclusively) accept Bitcoins for Teslas, and that it will =
keep a portion of its corporate cash in Bitcoin. Tesla, a big important com=
pany that Musk runs, is making real business decisions that seem to be bull=
ish for Bitcoin. If you buy Bitcoin based on Musk=E2=80=99s half-joking Twi=
tter enthusiasm, you could be making a sensible bet on business fundamental=
s.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When Elon Musk does Dogecoin things =E2=
=80=A6=C2=A0well, look, Dogecoin is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/23799615.262686/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL=
