ons as public-company CEOs. And then there=E2=80=99s Elon Musk, who just ge=
ts to keep talking like a visionary startup founder even though he runs a g=
iant public company.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think the trick is t=
o say=C2=A0<em>so much=C2=A0</em>nonsense that anyone who focuses on one pa=
rticular untrue statement looks a little silly: =E2=80=9CSure I said our ca=
rs would be fully self-driving this year, and that wasn=E2=80=99t true, but=
